*Interactive UI (Page 4 of 6)*

=== Buttons with `sendi` ===
Example:
`(sendi #! "Choose" "Yes:yes_macro" "No:no_macro")`

Each button maps to a macro name (saved or local).
Local macros work too - code is embedded in the button:
```
(begin
  (macro "yes" (send "you picked yes"))
  (sendi #! "choose" "yes:yes" "no:no")
)

=== Modals with `showui` ===
Example:
`(showui "Feedback" "save_feedback" "Rating" "Comment")`

`showui` requires an interactive trigger (typically from a button click).
Submitted field values become `args` in callback macro.

Use `/s7 help 5` for control flow.
